reviewText: It was a good movie. It was somewhat low budget,but not to much of an exploitation type film. It has a good message.

Typical person returns to their hometown where a large company is buying up the local land. Land owners are landing in the hospital.  Several actors in their younger years like Seymour Cassel and the deputy who played the manager on Major Leagues. Typical low budget Roger Corman movie that I had seen at the drive-in.

It's great that they released this on DVD finally, but I would have liked to have seen a few special features, but it's honestly fine without any. The movie is amazing, I've been a fan since I saw this as a kid, and the movie has held up great! 5 stars for the movie, 4 stars for the DVD.
MY FRIEND IS A COLLECTOR OF OLDER MOVIES AND SOME ARE ADVERTISED NEW AND ARE NOT.  THIS WAS JUST PERFECT, PRICE GOOD AND SHIPPING FAST.  ANOTHER HAPPY CUSTOMER!  THX!
